Compared with the native D99–E374 interaction, the advantage of studying the 172–399 interaction is that varying charge type at residue 399 had no obvious effect on channel activation when residue 172 remained neutral (Fig. 4 A). This suggests that the charges at residue 399 affect channel activation only when an electrostatic interaction is established with the charges at residue 172. On the other hand, the effects of charges at residue 172 are more complicated because varying charge type at residue 172 still was able to change the G-V relation when

