but with larger intervals at low [Ca2+]i for N172R/ E399R, such that the G-V curves cluster at high [Ca2+]i (Fig. 5, E and F). Consistently, the distribution of G-V
curves of N172R/E399C shows intermediate distribu-
tion along the voltage axis (Fig. 5, D and F). On the
other hand, the slope of G-V relations does not vary significantly at different [Ca2+]i or among different mutant channels (Fig. 5, C–F). These results indicate that the
BK channel becomes more sensitive to both saturating and intermediate [Ca2+]i when the 172–399 interaction changes from attraction to repulsion. Based on the
above experiments, we conclude that both voltage- and

